    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-05T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-05T05:00:00-05:00" n="389"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d389">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860I.00/432: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Estonia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leonard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tallinn</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-05T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 5, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received July 5—11:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. I have been informed confidentially that the visit of the Soviet official
                    mentioned in my telegram No. 80<note n="59" xml:id="d389fn59">Dated July 2, 5
                        p.m., not printed; it advised of the second visit of Andrey Alexandrovich
                        Zhdanov to Tallinn, where his presence caused uneasiness (740.0011 E. W.
                        1939/4356).</note> is in connection with the (1) extension of coast and
                    island defenses and reorganization of the Estonian Army, (2) elections to be
                    held for Parliament and (3) possible change in the person of the President of
                    Estonia, probably after the elections.</p>
                <p>Dates of elections not yet announced but will probably be held soon, after which
                    radical political changes may be expected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leonard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
